<h2>Software Artifacts and Datasets</h2>
<br/>
	<ul>
		
    <li> <a href="https://github.com/Rezar/ubiqlog">Ubiqlog </a> is an open source smartphone lifelogging tool that I did for my Ph.D. and now is available open-source. By running UbiqLog for about two months on 35 users, we have created a multivariate temporal dataset of smartphone sensors. The <a href="https://archive.ics.uci.edu/ml/datasets/UbiqLog+(smartphone+lifelogging)"> dataset</a> is available for public use. </li>
    <li> "insight for Wear" is our smartwatch lifelogging app that includes a very light predictive analytic mechanism. It has received some positive <a href="http://www.androidheadlines.com/2016/01/top-10-android-wear-apps-and-faces-january-2016-edition.html"> media attention and it is available in <a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.insight.insight"> Google Play</a>. </br> 
      </a>With respect to users we collect some smartwatch data and we do believe it is the largest dataset of wearable information available yet. For more information please check its <a href="http://insight4wear.com"> home page</a>.</li> 
	</ul>
